replaced by the Internationaler Fernschachbund (IFSB) in Berlin on 2 December
1928 by four Germans and a Dutchman. It became a federation of European
countries during the 1930's. Circa two-hundred European tournaments were
organised. Each year from 1929-38, a Bundesmeisterschaft (German Open) began. 
